      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Contract Awards\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Amount: $32.9B+ | Ticker: BA**\n\n---\n\nBoeing received two NASA contract awards totaling approximately **$32.9 billion** ($22.4B + $10.5B), representing among the largest single-entity NASA procurement actions on record, awarded to a company with an active federal contracting relationship spanning decades across DoD, NASA, and FAA regulatory frameworks. Boeing has received **$163+ billion in federal contracts since 2000** (USASpending.gov), including prior NASA contracts for the Space Launch System (SLS) that the Government Accountability Office flagged in 2023 for **$6 billion in cost overruns** and schedule failures with no contract termination action taken. Congressional oversight committees with jurisdiction over NASA appropriations include members who have historically received Boeing PAC contributions, a pattern documented by OpenSecrets across multiple election cycles totaling **millions in disclosed political donations**. Boeing's federal contracting record includes a 2021 DOJ deferred prosecution agreement over the 737 MAX fraud, a pattern consistent with regulatory capture documented by the Project On Government Oversight (POGO) in its federal contractor misconduct database.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:** USASpending.gov | GAO-23-106217 | OpenSecrets.org | POGO Federal Contractor Misconduct Database | DOJ Boeing DPA 2021\n\n*All figures from public record. No speculation included.*"
